@node "intro" "Intro"

This program sorts ASCII-lists with up to 10.000 items.


The features:

- sorts files with up to 10.000 items
- *very* easy to use (ASL-Requester)
- deletes blank characters
- deletes blank lines
- has a progress-bar
- displays how long it took to sort
- can print the destination-file on the printer
  (with or without line-numbers!)
- fast


@endnode


@node "install" "Installation"

How to install:


The WB-Version can be used without any installation.


@endnode


@node "require" "Requirements:"

You need:

- an AMIGA (obviously ;-)
- ASL-library for the WB-Version
- a printer if you want to print the results
- the CLI-commands "execute", "sort" and "wait"

@endnode


@node "usage" "Usage"

How to use:

SHARKsoft-WB can be run by double-clicking its icon. It's so
simple to use that I don't want to write a doc.

But I have to...

Double-click the icon, then select the file to sort.
In the next requester select the name of the sorted file.

When it's ready then a requester will appear. Here you can
select if you want to sort a 2nd file, print the actual
file or just quit the program.

That's it.

@endnode


