@node "history" "History"

New in 1.32 (October 3rd, 2001):

 - slightly improved speed by using
   a different approach in deleting
   blank characters.

- included the source-code


New in 1.30 (June 10th, 1998):

- removed the cli-version. If you miss it, contact me
  and I will reintroduce it in the next release.

- it now uses the DOS-command "sort" to sort the
  file. This makes it much faster. It is still very
  usable - much more than "sort". Also it still has
  the advantage, that it removes blank lines and chars.

- the WB-Version now has a progress-bar.

- it displays now how long it took to sort.


New in 1.21 (April 22nd, 1998):

- optimized the WB-Version in the same way as the CLI-Version in
  V1.20

- removed a bug (in the about-window the line "Deleted lines:"
  always ended with a "0" though this wasn't right. This bug was
  harmless.

- a (this) guide

- removed an unneccessary variable in the cli-Version. Now it needs
  less memory and diskspace... some bytes...


New in 1.20:

- checks first how many items to be sorted -> less memory hungry
  but a bit slower (needs to load the list twice)
  (only the CLI-Version)

- some optimizations (removed unnecessary variables)

- some corrections in the Readme-file.


New in 1.11:

- a very bad bug was removed. I'm very sorry that I have released
  SHARKsort in such a state (it crashed the system). I hope this
  will never happen again. It worked fine (as it should) but AFTER
  saving the file it crashed. This bug only appeared in the CLI-
  version and has been fixed.

- some corrections in the Readme.


New in 1.10 (January, 22nd, 1998):

- optimized the way how SHARKsort deletes characters and lines
  (in 1.0 it used two passes - now it's only one pass)

- added a CLI-version. The CLI-version cannot print a file on
  the printer. Also it doesn't use ASL-requestors. Instead you
  have to pass two arguments: "inputfile" and "outputfile".


Version 1.0 (January 18th, 1998):

- first public release

@endnode

@node "future" "Future"

Future developments:

At first: my ideas are already done. So if you have ideas and suggestions
for a next release of SHARKsort -> please contact me. You don't HAVE to
send a postcard if you want to make a suggestion -> just contact me via
E-Mail.

- Bugfixes if any bugs will appear

- PowerPC-support (not really needed, but: who knows?)

- for PPC-support I need a different programming-language
  at this time I'm still using the amazing Blitz Basic II.
  I really like the easy to use Requester- and Gadtools-
  handling. Also: it IS system-friendly!!!
  I'm waiting for a first PPC-Pascal or PPC-Modula2 or
  PPC-Oberon-compiler. Does anyone know of one?
  If I get hold of SAS/C 6.5 I would also try to do the
  next version in C. Anyone who wants to sell his copy?
  Please contact me!

- I still hope that Phoenix will become available within one year.

- your suggestions? PLEASE TELL ME WHAT YOU THINK IS MISSING!


@endnode

